The course of orthognathic surgery deals with the congenital and acquired deformations  of  jaws and their orthodontic and  surgical treatment. The subject consists of the overview of congenital abnormalities of facial skeleton, aetiology and pathogenesis, different techniques of surgical treatment and pre- and postsurgical orthodontic treatment. 
Subjects are covered in theoretical (lectures) and in practical work. Practical part consists of participation in seminars, consultations and  operations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of elective course is to teach orthodontic and surgical treatment methods of congenital and acquired deformations of jaws.

 Theoretical knowledge about congenital and acquired deformations of facial skeleton, aetiology ,pathogenesis, orthognatic and surgical treatment is discussed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  *knows diagnostics of ortognatic diseases and complete plan of treatment *knows indications of orthognatic surgical treatment *knows different techniques of ortohognatic surgical treatment
